  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601539468192-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601539468192-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601539468192-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601539468192-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1601539468192-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>and<strong> </strong>most<strong> </strong>of your <strong>Marmite</strong> (save a little for the mayo!) in a separate bowl – this is your <strong>speedy Marmite buttermilk</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601539484339-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601539484339-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601539484339-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601539484339-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1601539484339-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a large plate with the <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> dried oregano</strong>,<strong> ground allspice</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add a generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a few grinds of <strong>black pepper </strong>and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>spice mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
